The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Primary English push 

 Bangalore, Oct. 7 (PTI): 

 The JDS-BJP coalition government in Karnataka today announced 

 it will make English a compulsory subject from Class I from 

 the coming academic year.

 All schools, government and private, will impart English from first standard from June 2007, minister for primary and secondary education Basavaraj Horatti said after a cabinet meeting.

 In another step to implement its three-language formula, the government decided to make Kannada compulsory in all English-medium schools. 

 Kannada has also been made compulsory in schools run by linguistic minorities, which had the option to teach Kannada as an optional subject from Class III, he added.

 The minister said there was no change in the governments stand to derecognise more than 2,000 English-medium schools which had obtained permission as Kannada schools. 

 Because of the public outcry, these schools have been allowed to continue till March 2007.




